WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.000
Digital Tale of Genji - Feature Introduction.

00:00:03.000 --> 00:00:05.000
We will explain the AI Image Search.

00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:09.000
AI Image Search cross-searches manuscript images based on the Koigenji Monogatari,

00:00:09.000 --> 00:00:13.000
finding pages with high text similarity across multiple manuscripts and printed editions.

00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:15.000
It is useful for finding image data of specific scenes in the Tale of Genji.

00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:20.000
The registration status shows searchable manuscripts and editions listed by chapter.

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:24.000
Let us explain how similarity is calculated.

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:28.000
First, text data is attached to each image using kuzushiji OCR.

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:32.000
Then, the text data is compared with the Koigenji Monogatari at the double-page spread level.

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:35.000
Results are displayed in order of highest similarity.

00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:37.000
Here is how to access the search screen.

00:00:37.000 --> 00:00:41.000
Access it from "AI Image Search Edition" in the menu.

00:00:41.000 --> 00:00:43.000
Click the menu item on the left side.

00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:46.000
Click the search button.

00:00:46.000 --> 00:00:48.000
We will explain the search workflow.

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:50.000
Here are the steps to find image data of a specific scene.

00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:55.000
Step 1: Find the page in the Koigenji Monogatari that corresponds to the scene.

00:00:55.000 --> 00:00:59.000
Step 2: Select manuscript pages with high similarity.

00:00:59.000 --> 00:01:04.000
Step 3: Compare with the Koigenji Monogatari to confirm the correct page.

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:06.000
Let us start with Step 1.

00:01:06.000 --> 00:01:10.000
Search the text of the Koigenji Monogatari.

00:01:10.000 --> 00:01:14.000
Enter a word from the scene. For example, "inuki."

00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:17.000
You can narrow results by specifying a chapter.

00:01:17.000 --> 00:01:21.000
Search results are displayed.

00:01:21.000 --> 00:01:25.000
The Koigenji Monogatari image and text are shown.

00:01:25.000 --> 00:01:28.000
Confirm whether this is the page of the scene you are looking for.

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:31.000
Here are some search tips.

00:01:31.000 --> 00:01:35.000
Searches using different notation from the Koigenji Monogatari text will not produce hits.

00:01:35.000 --> 00:01:38.000
For example, searching "犬君" in kanji won't work; use "いぬき" in hiragana instead.

00:01:38.000 --> 00:01:42.000
Try switching between kanji and kana, with or without voiced marks.

00:01:42.000 --> 00:01:45.000
Now, Step 2.

00:01:45.000 --> 00:01:49.000
Select manuscript pages with high similarity scores.

00:01:49.000 --> 00:01:53.000
Select the manuscript pages to compare.

00:01:53.000 --> 00:01:57.000
The similarity calculation results are displayed.

00:01:57.000 --> 00:02:01.000
Items colored yellow are pages included in the Koigenji Monogatari.

00:02:01.000 --> 00:02:05.000
Traffic light icons indicate secondary use conditions.

00:02:05.000 --> 00:02:09.000
The Todai manuscript shows candidates at 46% and 41% similarity.

00:02:09.000 --> 00:02:13.000
Candidates from the University of Tokyo Faculty of Letters collection are also shown.

00:02:13.000 --> 00:02:17.000
Manuscript images are loading.

00:02:17.000 --> 00:02:21.000
Similarity scores are displayed for each manuscript.

00:02:21.000 --> 00:02:25.000
Secondary use condition icons can also be confirmed.

00:02:25.000 --> 00:02:29.000
Manuscripts from Tsukuba University and the Imperial Household Agency are also shown.

00:02:29.000 --> 00:02:33.000
Images of the Koigenji Monogatari page and high-similarity pages are displayed.

00:02:33.000 --> 00:02:37.000
You can compare manuscripts from different collections.

00:02:37.000 --> 00:02:41.000
Click a page number to display the manuscript image.

00:02:41.000 --> 00:02:45.000
Now, Step 3.

00:02:45.000 --> 00:02:49.000
Compare with the Koigenji Monogatari to confirm the correct page.

00:02:49.000 --> 00:02:53.000
It can be difficult to confirm content from images alone.

00:02:53.000 --> 00:02:57.000
Comparing the body text is recommended.

00:02:57.000 --> 00:03:01.000
Select "Compare by Text."

00:03:01.000 --> 00:03:05.000
Click "String Similarity Comparison."

00:03:05.000 --> 00:03:09.000
The comparison tool is loading.

00:03:09.000 --> 00:03:13.000
The text comparison tool is now displayed.

00:03:13.000 --> 00:03:17.000
Koigenji Monogatari text on the left, selected image text on the right.

00:03:17.000 --> 00:03:21.000
Comparison results are shown in the center.

00:03:21.000 --> 00:03:25.000
Continuing with text comparison.

00:03:25.000 --> 00:03:29.000
The "Image" tab shows the Koigenji Monogatari and manuscript images side by side.

00:03:29.000 --> 00:03:33.000
The "Text (Diff)" tab shows text differences.

00:03:33.000 --> 00:03:37.000
Blue lines indicate corresponding sections between the texts.

00:03:37.000 --> 00:03:41.000
Here are some additional features.

00:03:41.000 --> 00:03:45.000
Links to related materials.

00:03:45.000 --> 00:03:49.000
A link to the Koigenji Monogatari at the National Diet Library.

00:03:49.000 --> 00:03:53.000
A link to the Shinpen Nihon Koten Bungaku Zenshu on JapanKnowledge.

00:03:53.000 --> 00:03:57.000
The Koigenji Monogatari text viewer is displayed.

00:03:57.000 --> 00:04:01.000
The corresponding page in the National Diet Library Digital Collection opens.

00:04:01.000 --> 00:04:05.000
A scanned image of the Koigenji Monogatari is displayed.

00:04:05.000 --> 00:04:09.000
The link to the Shinpen Nihon Koten Bungaku Zenshu is also available.

00:04:09.000 --> 00:04:13.000
You can view the corresponding section on JapanKnowledge Lib.

00:04:13.000 --> 00:04:15.000
Here is how to check secondary use conditions.

00:04:15.000 --> 00:04:17.000
Traffic light icons indicate the conditions.

00:04:17.000 --> 00:04:19.000
Green means free use, yellow means conditional, red means application required.

00:04:19.000 --> 00:04:22.000
About the heart button.

00:04:22.000 --> 00:04:25.000
Click it when the result matches what you are looking for.

00:04:25.000 --> 00:04:28.000
The number of hearts serves as a guide to similarity.

00:04:28.000 --> 00:04:31.000
Login is required to use this feature.

00:04:31.000 --> 00:04:34.000
Please check the privacy policy for handling of authentication information.

00:04:34.000 --> 00:04:37.000
Digital Tale of Genji.

00:04:37.000 --> 00:04:40.000
Thank you for watching.
